WEBVTT

00:00.458 --> 00:01.437
There are two kinds of folks

00:01.464 --> 00:03.064
who sit around thinking
about how to kill people:

00:03.398 --> 00:05.124
psychopaths
and mystery writers.

00:05.362 --> 00:06.384
I'm the kind that pays better.

00:06.785 --> 00:07.385
Who am I?

00:07.474 --> 00:08.613
I'm Rick Castle.

00:08.614 --> 00:09.014
Castle.

00:09.048 --> 00:09.708
Castle.

00:09.709 --> 00:11.709
I really am ruggedly handsome,
aren't I?

00:11.855 --> 00:14.045
Every writer needs  inspiration.
And I found mine.

00:14.255 --> 00:15.074
Detective Kate Beckett.

00:15.109 --> 00:16.129
- Beckett.
- Beckett.

00:16.164 --> 00:18.070
- Nikki Heat?
- The character he's basing on you.

00:18.116 --> 00:19.602
And thanks to my friendship
with the mayor,

00:19.603 --> 00:20.603
I get to be on her case.

00:20.637 --> 00:22.580
I would be happy
to let you spank me.

00:22.615 --> 00:23.491
And together, we catch killers

00:24.439 --> 00:25.427
We make a pretty
good team, you know?

00:25.428 --> 00:26.428
Like Starsky and Hutch.

00:26.562 --> 00:27.256
Turner and Hooch.

00:27.619 --> 00:29.219
You do remind me
a little of Hooch.

00:34.243 --> 00:38.138
♪ 7 stars in the sky,
in the sky ♪

00:38.173 --> 00:40.204
Yeah, Paula,
that sounds perfect.

00:40.238 --> 00:41.736
Yeah, close the deal.

00:41.771 --> 00:43.501
Thank you. And to you.

00:43.535 --> 00:45.866
Hey.
Hey.

00:45.900 --> 00:48.730
Ask me why I'm here.
You know, I ask myself
that question every day.

00:48.765 --> 00:50.630
That was Paula, my agent,
with big news

00:50.665 --> 00:52.862
about my book "Heat Wave."
mm-hmm.

00:52.897 --> 00:55.694
Wanna guess?
Guessing would imply caring.

00:55.729 --> 00:57.195
I'll give you a hint.

00:57.228 --> 00:59.128
The headlines in the trades
might read,

00:59.162 --> 01:04.525
"Castle best seller
to 'heat' up big screen."

01:04.560 --> 01:06.557
Your book is being made
into a movie?

01:06.591 --> 01:08.557
And you are about to be
immortalized

01:08.591 --> 01:10.457
on the silver screen.

01:10.492 --> 01:14.492
Actually, Nikki Heat is going
to be immortalized, not me.
Yes, well, technically,

01:14.527 --> 01:17.095
but it's been widely publicized
that you are the inspiration.

01:17.129 --> 01:19.592
So who would you like
to play you in the movie?
whoa. Are you kidding?

01:19.626 --> 01:21.357
They're really making
a Nikki Heat movie?

01:21.391 --> 01:23.625
Dude, did I call it or what?
Ah, congrats, bro.

01:23.830 --> 01:25.731
Thank you!
What do you think,

01:25.765 --> 01:28.198
can we get James McAvoy
for Detective Raley?

01:28.232 --> 01:30.198
I'm gonna go
with Javier Bardem.
Beckett.

01:30.233 --> 01:32.696
In your casting dreams.
Yes, I'd like to report a murder.

01:33.943 --> 01:35.609
Do you have an address?

01:35.794 --> 01:37.994
Where's the fun in that?

01:38.028 --> 01:40.061
<i>Okay.</i>

01:41.070 --> 01:42.735
Who is this?

01:42.770 --> 01:44.102
Oh, a fan.

01:44.137 --> 01:47.436
Tell me more about this murder.
Tracing.

01:47.470 --> 01:48.870
Well, I did it.

01:48.904 --> 01:50.904
And that's all
you need to know.

01:50.938 --> 01:52.371
Got it.

01:52.405 --> 01:54.705
Hello?
42nd and Lex.

01:54.739 --> 01:57.139
That's Grand Central Station.
Yeah, let's go.

01:58.680 --> 01:59.980
According to tech,

02:00.014 --> 02:02.747
The phone call came from
the second booth on the end.

02:04.000 --> 02:10.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

02:29.644 --> 02:31.010
Here's his wallet.

02:32.812 --> 02:33.612
Thank you.

02:33.747 --> 02:34.646
You got it.

02:34.793 --> 02:37.359
His name's Alex Peterman,
lives in Dobbs Ferry.

02:37.393 --> 02:39.460
So it wasn't a robbery.

02:39.494 --> 02:41.028
He's a personal injury attorney.

02:41.062 --> 02:42.428
Taking the late train home.

02:42.463 --> 02:43.963
Anything
other than G.S.W.S?

02:43.997 --> 02:47.365
Nope, just the 5 shots
to the chest from a .45.

02:47.399 --> 02:49.933
A .45 makes a pretty loud
snap, crackle and pop.

02:49.968 --> 02:52.535
I find it hard to believe no one
heard it on the main concourse.

02:52.945 --> 02:54.245
He must have used
a suppressor

02:54.270 --> 02:56.071
and waited for the train
to pass by.

02:56.081 --> 02:57.781
And let's face it--
New Yorkers are famous

02:57.805 --> 03:00.272
for their "hear no evil,
see no evil" attitude.

03:00.306 --> 03:01.539
I'll give you a call
with an update

03:01.540 --> 03:03.741
once I get him back to the lab.
Thank you.

03:03.775 --> 03:06.943
Quick--who do you want to play
you in the Nikki Heat movie?
Halle Berry.

03:06.977 --> 03:09.843
See? Some people
are just great at that game.

03:09.877 --> 03:13.077
You know who we could get
for you? Angelina. No.

03:13.112 --> 03:15.946
Kate Beckett,
Kate Beckinsale.

03:15.980 --> 03:17.947
We'll call you K-Becks.

03:17.981 --> 03:19.983
Hey, guys,
where are we on the case?

03:19.993 --> 03:21.813
We got a woman
who says that she heard

03:21.817 --> 03:23.417
a loud sound around 8:45--

03:23.452 --> 03:25.286
sounded like
a car door slamming.

03:25.296 --> 03:26.296
And she said she saw
a white male,

03:26.320 --> 03:29.755
30s, average height,
exiting the waiting room,

03:29.790 --> 03:31.192
moving very quickly
to the 42nd street exit.

03:31.202 --> 03:34.002
Said he was wearing a black
coat, black ball cap, sunglasses

03:34.627 --> 03:36.494
and had some sort of beard,
maybe a goatee.

03:36.528 --> 03:38.929
All right, let's see if anyone
can corroborate her description,

03:38.963 --> 03:41.531
and let's make up a sketch, show
it to Alex Peterman's family,

03:41.565 --> 03:44.099
See if they recognize the killer.
Right.

03:47.301 --> 03:48.601
What is it?

03:50.336 --> 03:52.671
He called
to report his crime.

03:52.705 --> 03:55.039
And that voice...

03:55.073 --> 03:58.374
it's like
he did this for fun.

04:05.514 --> 04:07.514
Hey.
You're up early.

04:07.548 --> 04:09.982
Yes, I have a date
with Beckett at the morgue.

04:10.016 --> 04:12.916
What nefarious plots
are you two hatching?
Uh--

04:12.951 --> 04:14.950
My birthday is coming up.

04:14.984 --> 04:16.817
Uh-huh.

04:16.851 --> 04:19.152
I think
you should tell him, gram.

04:19.185 --> 04:21.019
Sometimes he gives
good advice.

04:21.053 --> 04:23.486
Sometimes?
Yeah, maybe you're right.

04:23.520 --> 04:25.920
But I am not in the mood for
any of your cavalier quips.

04:26.055 --> 04:27.389
I'll be serious
as a shark attack.

04:27.399 --> 04:29.399
Chet has asked me
to move in with him.

04:31.124 --> 04:33.858
I told her... that I thought
it was too soon.

04:33.892 --> 04:35.794
They've only been dating
a few months.

04:35.885 --> 04:38.687
When you get to be our age,
every minute counts.

04:38.721 --> 04:41.790
To that end, I have made
a list of pros and cons.

04:41.824 --> 04:43.525
So far the pros are winning.

04:43.559 --> 04:46.494
"pro-- he makes me feel young."
well...

04:46.528 --> 04:49.597
I make you feel young.
Oh, darling.

04:49.631 --> 04:52.566
"cons--I don't want to live
in another man's home."

04:52.601 --> 04:55.569
You are not another man.
Besides, I trained you.

04:55.604 --> 04:57.905
Who knows what bad habits

04:57.939 --> 04:59.974
Chet picked up along the way,
you know?
Mm-hmm.

05:00.122 --> 05:02.289
Mother, whatever you decide,
I will support you,

05:03.142 --> 05:04.811
the same way I have since
the last man you lived with

05:05.049 --> 05:06.783
stole your life savings.

05:09.470 --> 05:11.471
Cause of death
is multiple gunshot wounds.

05:11.505 --> 05:14.708
Tox indicates he had a martini
about an hour before he died.

05:14.742 --> 05:16.075
Other than that,

05:16.109 --> 05:18.777
there is nothing interesting
about the body.

05:18.812 --> 05:20.779
So then why the call?

05:20.814 --> 05:23.515
The body isn't interesting.
Excuse me.

05:23.549 --> 05:25.116
But the bullets are.

05:25.150 --> 05:26.251
Check out the marking
on the end of the slugs.

05:26.423 --> 05:27.990
Aftermarket factory stamps?

05:28.025 --> 05:29.258
No.

05:29.293 --> 05:32.128
Those aren't stamps.
They're letters.

05:33.602 --> 05:36.637
And look,
they're hand-etched.

05:38.340 --> 05:40.107
They spell something.

05:40.141 --> 05:41.741
They spell...

05:41.776 --> 05:43.776
"kinki."

05:46.079 --> 05:47.612
No.

05:53.185 --> 05:54.652
"Nikki."

05:54.687 --> 05:56.487
Nikki Heat.

05:58.157 --> 06:00.125
That's why he called me.

06:00.159 --> 06:02.094
That's why he said
he was a fan.

06:02.128 --> 06:04.597
He dedicated
this murder to me.

06:06.064 --> 06:08.133
Does he realize she's a fictional
character not a real person?

06:08.324 --> 06:11.327
Obviously, he's delusional,
but given that Nikki Heat

06:11.361 --> 06:13.629
is based on Detective Beckett,
maybe he's confusing the two.

06:13.663 --> 06:14.829
And we showed
Alex Peterman's family

06:14.975 --> 06:16.308
the sketch of our suspect.
He did not look familiar.

06:17.552 --> 06:18.819
How are we on forensics?

06:19.059 --> 06:20.626
C.S.U. grabbed
about 200 fingerprints,

06:20.660 --> 06:22.894
a thousand fibers
and 60 odd D.N.A. samples,

06:22.929 --> 06:25.363
and that was
just from the phone box.

06:25.397 --> 06:28.733
They're working them up now...
after they clear their backlog.

06:28.767 --> 06:32.568
Beckett. Guy on the phone's
asking for Detective heat.

06:39.493 --> 06:40.859
Beckett.

06:40.894 --> 06:44.629
Nikki, did you get
the first part of my message?

06:44.664 --> 06:46.497
Yes, I did.

06:46.532 --> 06:50.467
Well, the second is
at the Central Park carousel.

07:48.147 --> 07:50.847
<font color=#7FFF00>♪ Castle 2x17 ♪</font>
